text.section:
An entity subject to this section:
shall classify an obstetrician/gynecologist as a primary care provider; or
if the obstetrician/gynecologist chooses not to be a primary care provider, shall allow a woman to receive routine gynecological care from an in-network obstetrician/gynecologist without requiring the woman to visit a primary care provider first, if:
the care is medically necessary, including care that is routine;
after each visit for gynecological care, the obstetrician/gynecologist communicates with the woman's primary care provider about any diagnosis or treatment rendered; and
the obstetrician/gynecologist confers with the primary care provider before performing any diagnostic procedure that is not routine gynecological care rendered during an annual visit.
